---
description: Enforce endpoint-per-directory route file structure in server routes
globs: src/server/lib/routes/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: true
---

# Route File Structure Rule

Use this rule whenever creating or restructuring routes under `src/server/lib/routes`.

## Required route contract

Each endpoint must live in its own directory and include:

- `<endpoint-name>.route.ts`
- `<endpoint-name>.config.ts`
- `<endpoint-name>.handler.ts`
- `index.ts`
- `schemas/` directory with `index.ts` and relevant `*.schema.ts` files

## Group-level contract

Each route group directory (for example `files`, `health`, `me`, `video`) must have:

- `index.ts` that composes child routers and optional group middleware
- No endpoint business logic in group-level `index.ts`

## Endpoint-level contract

Inside each endpoint directory:

- Exactly one route registration file (`<endpoint>.route.ts`)
- Route file only wires `config + handler` via `router.openapi(...)`
- Config file defines the OpenAPI route contract (`createRoute`)
- Handler file contains runtime behavior (`RouteHandler`)
- `schemas/index.ts` only re-exports schema/type symbols

## Naming constraints

- Endpoint directory names are kebab-case and intent-based (`get-token`, `docs-by-session-id`, `patch-profile`)
- Schema files must be singular and explicit:
  - `body.schema.ts`
  - `query.schema.ts`
  - `params.schema.ts`
  - `response.schema.ts`
  - `error.schema.ts`
- Never use plural schema filenames such as `*.schemas.ts`

## Barrel file rules

- Endpoint `index.ts` re-exports only endpoint-local files (`route`, `config`, `handler`, `schemas`)
- Group `index.ts` composes endpoint routers using `route('', childRouter)` (or explicit prefix where required)
- Root `src/server/lib/routes/index.ts` mounts only route groups
